translated:
Ödquist, Carl Oscar, vicar, Jönköping, b. 28/2/80 in Jönköp. to sea captain Olof Ö. and Matilda Persson. M. 12/xx with Emilia Sellström. Children: Gunnar b. 1913, Bengt b. 1916, Margareta b. 1918, Ulla b. 1921. — Graduated from Palmgren High School in Stockholm in 1904, theology and philosophy degrees from Uppsala in 1906, theological candidate, practical theology exam, ordained priest for the Växjö diocese, and elementary school teacher exam in 1908. Deputy pastor in Jönköping from 1909-1911, pastor in Jönköping from 1911, first curate from 1915, parish priest in Kristina parish in Jönköping since 1925, archpriest in Tveta archpriestry since 1933, preacher at the poorhouse institution in Jönköping from 1911-1920, regimental pastor in Småland Artillery Regiment from 1915-1927. Inspector of Jönköping high school from 1929, chairman of the school board, former chairman of the board for public elementary school, vice chairman of the child welfare committee, etc., missionary representative for Jönköping parish. Writings: essays and sermons in various publications. Recipient of the Royal Order of Vasa. 

Öfverström, Thorsten, magistrate. Bollebygd, b. 1/xx03 in Ulricehamn to transport company owner Julius Ö. and Ada Mårtensson. M. 1/xx with Annie Hultin, deceased; 2/19xx with Hjördlis Lundh. Children: Nils Thorsten b. 1932, Ingrid Margareta b. 1935, Leif Thorsten b. 1942, Eva Margareta b. 1948. — Completed secondary school exams in 1920, graduated from the magistrate academy in 1928. Employed at the county chancellery in 1927, assistant magistrate in Vättle district from 1929, magistrate in Kungsäter district from 1938, in Grums from 1942, in Bollebygd from 1945. Member of the Association of Swedish Magistrates and its Älvsborg branch.
